reviews.review: Awesome ending to an amazing saga

The ending was horrible, to many side characters were not relevant. I wish Disney would have never bought the franchise it just made it all commercial and took away the original creativity by catering to the masses.

This movie was a non- stop action / emotional roller coaster. There were  shocking revelations and heartrending deaths! Some choices I did not agree with ( no spoilers) but I did appreciate that so many characters & storylines  were addressed...

I enjoyed it. But a few things I felt amiss
Spoiler alert
I feel like they hinted that rey might use a staff version of lighsaber like darth maul's  ie during the training she was more comfortable to use her staff than lightsaber and acquiring leia and luke lightsaber, can combine both, but was ultimately ignored. Still confuse as in why they hinted possible  love triangle between rose, rey and the storm trooper guy but was ultimately ignored with no resolution.. Other than that I love the movie

I did like that there was some conclusion to the whole series. But overall I did not like this movie at all. Major plot holes, tons of stuff that didn’t make sense or wasn’t consistent with characters past. Please stop making these movies Disney
Absolutely loved  it!! Nostalgic and good wrap up to end it all.
Excellent movie, outstanding special effects with closure to the Star Wars Saga!
It was fun but it did not leave me as excited about the franchise as the last two movies did. Also the romantic subplots were handled weird
Not bad on wrapping things up, a lot crammed in. Sad the saga is over, hard to end something this good on a stellar note.

The Star Wars saga has, for decades, taken us through highs and lows and we all had high expectations for this last movie while secretly expecting to be disappointed... but we were not disappointed! Yes, they push the laws of science and some scenes really require us to “just go with it” but the overarching story hit the spot and the actors brought back filled our need for nostalgia. In a world where you will never please everybody, The Rise of Skywalker exceeded my expectations, grabbed my attention from the first to the last scene and even extracted my tears. The force is strong with this one!
